Osteosarcoma with cell-cycle and fibroblast growth factor genomic alterations: case report of Molecular Tumor Board combination strategy resulting in long-term exceptional response.
Treatment was given at reduced dosing (lenvatinib 10 mg oral daily (approved dose=24 mg daily)) and palbociclib 75 mg oral daily, one week on and one week off (approved dose=125 mg oral daily, three weeks on/one week off) and is tolerated well. Therefore, co-targeting the aberrant cyclin and FGFR pathways resulted in long-term exceptional response in a patient with refractory advanced osteosarcoma.
